    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Circling back on this. Auto-downloading/caching of plugins is still a great idea to implement, but in the interim, there might also be a good truffle box use case here. Plugin writers can streamline ease-of-use by boxing plugin-specific configs, use the box install/postinstall hook to set the user/dev up with their plugin package, _and_ output plugin-specific commands upon successful unboxing.",
